# Import data:
vanEmissions <- read_csv2("Data/VanEmissionsLong.csv")
## ℹ Using "','" as decimal and "'.'" as grouping mark. Use `read_delim()` for more control.
## Rows: 24 Columns: 3
## ── Column specification ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
## Delimiter: ";"
## chr (1): EmissionClass
## dbl (2): Year, Percentage
## 
## ℹ Use `spec()` to retrieve the full column specification for this data.
## ℹ Specify the column types or set `show_col_types = FALSE` to quiet this message.
# Convert doubles to factors
vanEmissions$Year <- factor(vanEmissions$Year)
vanEmissions$EmissionClass <- factor(vanEmissions$EmissionClass)
# Add your code here
str(vanEmissions)
## spc_tbl_ [24 × 3] (S3: spec_tbl_df/tbl_df/tbl/data.frame)
##  $ Year         : Factor w/ 3 levels "2020","2022",..: 3 3 3 3 3 3 3 3 2 2 ...
##  $ EmissionClass: Factor w/ 8 levels "0","1","2","3",..: 8 1 2 3 4 5 6 7 8 1 ...
##  $ Percentage   : num [1:24] 0 2 0 1 5 15 26 51 0 2 ...
##  - attr(*, "spec")=
##   .. cols(
##   ..   Year = col_double(),
##   ..   EmissionClass = col_character(),
##   ..   Percentage = col_double()
##   .. )
##  - attr(*, "problems")=<externalptr>
ggplot(vanEmissions, aes(x = Year, fill = EmissionClass)) +
  geom_col(aes(y = vanEmissions$Percentage), position = "dodge") +
  guides(fill=guide_legend(title="Emission Classes")) +
  labs(title = "Distribution of Emission Classes of Vans
in the Netherlands from 2020 to 2024 ",
x = "Year", y = "Percentage of Vans in Emission Class (%)") +
labs(caption = "*Notice the constant increase in % of vans in emission class 6, over the years. \n\n*The higher the number of the emission class, the
cleaner the vehicle.")
